**What it checks, in order:**

| Step | Check | Fail = skip? |
|------|-------|-------------|
| 1 | File exists, `.docx` extension, not 0 bytes | ✅ Hard stop |
| 2 | Valid ZIP archive structure | ✅ Hard stop |
| 3 | All critical XML parts present | ✅ Hard stop |
| 4 | Critical XML parses without errors | ✅ Hard stop |
| 5 | Optional XML (numbering, settings) parses | ⚠ Warning only |
| 6 | Relationship targets exist in ZIP | ⚠ Warning only |

**To use it in your existing flow**, just replace wherever you do `ModelDoc(filepath)` or `ValReport(filepath)` with a call to `process_documents(your_file_list)`, or call `validate_docx()` inline before each instantiation.
